Governor Abdullahi Sule of Nasarawa State, has approved the appointments of eight Senior Special Assistants, (SSAs). They are Samuel Egya, SSA Government House; Yakubu Kwanta, SSA youth affairs/non governmental organizations and Murtala Hassan Lamus, SSA Special Duties. Others are; Alhassan Abdullahi, SSA investment/economic planning; James Thomas, SSA Liaison Office Abuja; Hon. Rakiya Alaku – SSA Women affairs and empowerment; Salihu Isyaka Ogah- SSA deputy governor’s office and Barrister Abubakar Imam Zanuwa, SSA Legal matters. The appointments take effect from 1st June, 2019. Tambuwal appoints SSG, advisers Tambuwal appoints SSG, advisers Ex-Media Trust staff appointed SSA Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin